    "To ensure that the model fitted is explainable, some model-agnostic tools and techniques can be used.",
    "Examples of tools that can be used to assist the developer in explaining the model results include PDPs (Friedman, 2001), SHAP (Lundberg & Lee, 2017) values, and LIME (Ribeiro et al., 2016).",
